 The study will start with a single dose ascending (SAD) phase.

 LMG324 will be administered on Day 1 with no further treatment until implementation of standard of care (SoC) therapy.

 SoC therapy is ranibizumab 0.

5 mg administered per label.

 Dose groups will be implemented sequentially to allow for safety review between the current and subsequent dose group.

 All treatments will be open-label, including ranibizumab used as SoC therapy.

 In the enrollment expansion phase, subjects randomized to LMG324 arm will receive a single LMG324 IVT injection on Day 1 followed by sham (fake) IVT injections until implementation of SoC therapy.

 After implementation, SoC therapy will be applied monthly with sham injections applied at the interim planned visits.

 The enrollment expansion phase may start at a selected dose level whilst the dose escalation phase is still ongoing.

