The purpose of this first-in-human study is to evaluate the safety and tolerability of single ascending doses of LMG324 to determine the maximum tolerated dose (MTD) in neovascular age-related macular degeneration (nvAMD) subjects.

 Enrollment will be expanded at a safe and tolerated dose in treatment naive nvAMD subjects to compare a single intravitreal (IVT) dose of LMG324 to ranibizumab 0.

5 mg administered every 4 weeks for change from baseline in best-corrected visual acuity (BCVA) at Week 12 (Day 85).

